  "texts": [
    "(1), L represents the average loss, and model training aims to decrease this value.",
    "A lower loss indicates better image-generation quality.",
    "Ŷθ refers to the evolving diffusion model that continuously receives a noisy image vector α t Y + σ t ǫ and a text h, and produces a predicted image.",
    "This predicted image is compared to the truth image Y, and the difference between them is quantified as the loss.",
    "The error between the predicted and ground truth images is measured using the squared loss."
